This paper deals with the problem of supporting empirical probabilities in deductive databases, which is a topic that falls under the scope of database systems (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also presents a model-theoretic characterization of logic databases, which is related to mathematical logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses an algorithm for checking consistency and a query processing procedure, which are topics that are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and computational engineering (cs.CE).
